@startuml sequence-diagram
title Add Clothing Item with Automatic Background Removal

actor "User" as User
participant "Frontend\n(React + Vite)" as FE
participant "Backend API\n(FastAPI)" as API
participant "Rembg Service\n(U2-Net model)" as BG
database "PostgreSQL" as DB
collections "Uploads Volume\n(Docker Volume)" as FS

User -> FE: Select photo, submit "Add item"
FE -> API: POST /items (image, metadata)
activate API

API -> FS: Save raw image
API -> DB: Insert item row (status = "processing")
API --> FE: 202 Accepted (item id, status: processing)
deactivate API

API -> BG: Send image for background removal
activate BG

alt Background removal succeeds
    BG --> API: Return processed image (transparent bg)
    API -> FS: Save processed image
    API -> DB: Update item (status = "ready", image_url)
else Background removal fails or times out
    BG --> API: Error / timeout
    API -> DB: Update item (status = "fallback", image_url = original)
end
deactivate BG

FE -> API: GET /items/{id} (poll or refresh)
activate API
API -> DB: Read item status
API --> FE: 200 OK (item, current status)
deactivate API

FE --> User: Show item in wardrobe (processed or original image)

@enduml